<!-- Hey all, a week ago I looked at incoming photos on instagram and found it
pretty compelling.  Each photo is something someone finds valuable to share.
Individually the random stream of photos could be boring, but as a collection
it is a juxtaposition of snippets into peoples lives, and it is that
juxtaposition I find interesting. instagram photos on their own can be
beautiful because of the filters, so I wanted to see what many of them would be
like. 

As I built this I included a social component.  Many people only have 100-200
or so followers so many may not see the photo, you can interact by RTing the
photo, instead of just consuming them. 

After playing with it I found it offered insight into subculture specific memes
I would originally never see.  It encourages serendipity. 

I used this to also play a little with backbone js.  Tips to improve it with
respect to code design patterns are encouraged.

you can see my other projects at whichlight.com

Thanks! 

@kawantum -->



